data.description: The house built in 1976 is a split-level design, nestled in a quiet, tree-lined neighborhood. This timeless gem built in 1976 effortlessly combines the best of both worlds: classic charm and modern convenience. Step into this meticulously maintained residence, and you'll discover a home that's more than just four walls Co it's a piece of history waiting for its next chapter. The house has been upgraded with wood flooring throughout various areas, giving it a warm and inviting ambiance. The wood flooring adds a touch of elegance and is easy to maintain. The bathrooms in this house have been updated. They likely include new fixtures, such as sinks, toilets, and shower and bathtub. The kitchen has also been renovated. This will likely include new counter-tops, flooring, light fixture, island, and refrigerator. The house boasts a pool, which provides a great recreational place to relax, leisure and enjoy outdoor activities. The pool has been well-maintained, and the liner has been updated. The backyard offers plenty of space for outdoor activities, whether it's hosting BBQs, gardening, or simply lounging by the pool. Overall, this house combines the charm of its 1970s split-level design with modern updates in key areas like the wood flooring, bathrooms, and kitchen. Conveniently located near schools, parks, shopping centers, supermarkets, restaurants and major highways, making commuting a breeze. Don't miss the opportunity to make this well-loved, vintage house your forever home. Schedule a viewing today and step into a piece of history reimagined for modern living. No HOA. Excellent schools in the area provide quality education options for families.
